📊 Dataset

The dataset used for training and evaluating the Landslide Detection Model contains satellite images and corresponding segmentation masks used for supervised learning.

Due to GitHub's file size limitations, the dataset (576 MB) is hosted externally on Google Drive.

🔗 Dataset Download Link

Access the dataset here:

Google Drive:
https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/14Y99Rb-DAT0YLK8ROCfvC0QEcPEL7AMW?usp=sharing

📁 Dataset Contents

The dataset includes:

Training Images – Satellite images used to train the model

Training Masks – Ground truth landslide segmentation masks

Validation Data – Used for model validation

Test Data – Used for evaluating model performance

📦 Dataset Format

The dataset is stored in NumPy format (.npy) for efficient training.

Example structure:

data/
│
├── trainX.npy
├── trainY.npy
├── valX.npy
├── valY.npy
├── testX.npy
└── testY.npy
📏 Dataset Size

Total Size: 576 MB

Image Size: 128 × 128 pixels

Channels: 4 (RGB + NIR)

⚠️ Note

The dataset is provided for educational and research purposes related to landslide detection and environmental monitoring.
